Context: The Culinary Skills (Preparatory Training) program information sessions are held regularly at the Hospitality Building of George Brown College. Interested individuals can contact auged@georgebrown.ca or 416-415-5000, ext. 6790 to learn about program content, career options, and meet professors and staff. Currently, no information sessions are scheduled. To receive updates on application deadlines, college news, upcoming events, and tours, visitors can sign up on the website. Other contact details include 416-415-2000 for general inquiries and TTY: 1-877-515-5559 for hearing impaired individuals. The college's social media hub is also available for further information. Please note that the information on the website is subject to change without notice, and students are responsible for verifying George Brown College fee requirements.
